Major Responsibilities

Assist in preparing procedural and relevant documents including the clearing house rules, operating procedures and agreements with business partners etc. to facilitate the implementation of new initiatives or services enhancements relating to Clearing House Automated Transfer System (CHATS), Faster Payment System (FPS) and other interbank clearing and settlement services for retail payments;
liaise with external parties, e.g. the HKMA, HKAB, the settlement institutions or clearing banks, member banks, business partners and legal advisers, etc., in devising the above-mentioned documents;
assist in exploring and developing new business and services improvement opportunities;
assess and analyse the feasibility of proposed initiatives from business and operational perspective;
assist in planning, coordinating and managing the implementation of new initiatives or services enhancements from business users’ perspective;
liaise with internal teams to clarify system design and to devise operation processes and contingency arrangements;
compile presentation materials and conduct cross-departmental or external presentations for banks or financial institutions to facilitate the implementation of new initiatives or services enhancements; and
perform other duties as assigned
Requirements

University education in business administration, banking or finance-related discipline or information technology;
3 to 5 years’ experience in financial sector with relevant experience in project management and drafting of procedural and/or legal documents preferred, prior exposure to product/operation management in financial institutions and/or clearing and settlement systems is an advantage;
strong business analytical and project management skills;
good command of written English, and fluency in spoken English and Putonghua; and
able to work under pressure to meet the tight timelines.
How to Apply
Interested parties please send your curriculum vitae stating your current and expected salaries, and the contact phone number to the Human Resources Division, Unit B, 25/F, MG Tower, 133 Hoi Bun Road, Kwun Tong, Kowloon  by clicking the "Apply Now" button below.
All applications and personal information collected will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for the purpose of recruitment and selection.  The information collected will be accessed by our authorized personnel only.  Those applicants not contacted by the Human Resources Division within two months from their application date should consider their applications filed for future reference which will be retained for one year for possible future job matching, and will be destroyed after the expiry of one year.

Job Duties:

Responsible for end-to-end payment solutions, online payment solutions management;
Responsible for payment solutions (Local payment gateway, Credit card payment gateway, cryptocurrency payment gateway & etc) integrations: price negotiations, contract terms negotiations, gathering user requirements, testing and launch plan;
Operation flow setup and finance-related management;
Payment gateway accounts performance management;
Fraud Monitoring and Prevention services;
Chargeback and dispute handling services;
Checkout optimization in terms of experience, behaviors and cost;
Other ad-hoc task as assigned.
What we need from you:

Degree or above;
Strong knowledge in payment process;
Proficient in both Written & Spoken English & Cantonese (including Mandarin);
Strong sense of responsibility & accountability;
Self-driven, detail-oriented & highly resilient.
What we offer:

Attractive Package (Double Pay + Quarterly Bonus + Year end Bonus)
Learning, Study & Travel Allowances
Office Hour (10:00 – 18:30, Mon – Fri)
Transparent and friendly working environment
Work location: Kowloon East (6-8 mins from MTR station)
Interested parties please submit your full resume with current and expected salary via "Apply Now". 

 (We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. All information provided will be treated strictly confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.)

